  </button></template><md-icon aria-hidden="true"><template shadowrootmode="open"><!----><slot></slot></template>keyboard_arrow_down</md-icon></md-icon-button><h3>4.4 SVD &amp; Dimensionality Reduction</h3></div>
<ol>
<li>Create a random 4×3 matrix <code>X</code> (use <code>np.random.seed(42)</code>).</li>
<li>Compute its <strong>SVD</strong>: <code>U, S, Vt = np.linalg.svd(X, full_matrices=False)</code>.</li>
<li><strong>Reconstruct</strong> <code>X</code> from the SVD and verify it matches the original.</li>
<li>Perform a <strong>rank-1 approximation</strong> using only the largest singular value/vector — call it <code>X_approx</code>.</li>
<li>Explain the relationship between SVD components and PCA in the markdown cell below.</li>
</ol>
</span></div>
