<p><strong>Scenario:</strong> You suspect that Engineering salaries are significantly higher than the company average.</p>
<ol>
<li>State the <strong>null hypothesis H₀</strong> and <strong>alternative hypothesis H₁</strong>.</li>
<li>Run a <strong>one-sample t-test</strong> comparing Engineering salaries against the overall mean salary.</li>
<li>Interpret the p-value at α = 0.05.</li>
<li>Also compute the <strong>Pearson correlation</strong> between <code>salary</code> and <code>years_exp</code>, and interpret it.</li>
</ol>
</span></div>
        </div>
