<ol>
<li>Generate two samples: <code>s1</code> ~ Normal(0, 1), <code>s2</code> ~ Exponential(1), both n=200 (seed=0).</li>
<li>Run the <strong>Kolmogorov-Smirnov test</strong> (<code>stats.kstest</code>) comparing each against a standard normal CDF.</li>
<li>Generate a non-stationary time series (linear trend + noise). Run the <strong>Augmented Dickey-Fuller test</strong> (<code>adfuller</code> from <code>statsmodels</code>) and interpret the result.</li>
<li>Difference the series once and re-run ADF to confirm stationarity.</li>
</ol>
</span></div>
