  </button></template><md-icon aria-hidden="true"><template shadowrootmode="open"><!----><slot></slot></template>keyboard_arrow_down</md-icon></md-icon-button><h3>6.3 Bayes' Theorem</h3></div>
<p><strong>Scenario — Spam filter:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>P(Spam) = 0.30 (prior)</li>
<li>P("free" | Spam) = 0.80 (likelihood)</li>
<li>P("free" | Not Spam) = 0.05</li>
</ul>
<ol>
<li>Compute P(Spam | "free") using Bayes' theorem.</li>
<li>Implement a simple <code>naive_bayes_predict(prior_spam, p_word_given_spam, p_word_given_ham)</code> that returns the posterior P(Spam | word).</li>
<li>In the markdown cell, map each term — <strong>prior, likelihood, evidence, posterior</strong> — to the spam example.</li>
</ol>
</span></div>
        </div>
