        <div class="text-top-div">
          <div class="markdown"><span><p><strong>Bayes Term Mapping (6.3):</strong></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Term</th>
<th>Formula</th>
<th>In this example</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>Prior</td>
<td>P(Spam)</td>
<td>0.30 (initial probability that an email is spam)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Likelihood</td>
<td>P(word | Spam)</td>
<td>P("free" | Spam) = 0.80 (how often "free" appears in spam emails)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Evidence</td>
<td>P(word)</td>
<td>P("free") = overall probability of seeing "free" in any email</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Posterior</td>
<td>P(Spam | word)</td>
<td>P(Spam | "free") = updated probability that an email is spam after observing "free"</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</span></div>
