  </button></template><md-icon aria-hidden="true"><template shadowrootmode="open"><!----><slot></slot></template>keyboard_arrow_down</md-icon></md-icon-button><h3>6.4 Central Limit Theorem</h3></div>
<ol>
<li>Define a population following an <strong>exponential distribution</strong> (λ=1, size=100,000).</li>
<li>Repeatedly draw samples of size <code>n=30</code> and record their means — do this 5,000 times.</li>
<li>Plot the histogram of sample means.</li>
<li>Overlay the <strong>theoretical normal distribution</strong> predicted by the CLT: μ = population mean, σ = population_std / sqrt(n).</li>
<li>Run a KS test to confirm the distribution of sample means is approximately normal.</li>
</ol>
</span></div>
