        <div class="text-top-div">
          <div class="markdown"><span><p><strong>CLT Reflection (6.4):</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Central Limit Theorem is important because it shows that sample means tend to follow a normal distribution even when the underlying data is not normal, as long as the sample size is large enough. This makes it possible to use normal-based inference methods reliably in practice.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In statistics and machine learning, CLT justifies the assumption of approximate normality of estimators (like means and regression coefficients), which is the foundation for many classical hypothesis tests, confidence intervals, and parametric models.</p>
</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

